om/repos/libgdx/libgdx/issues/3254","id":118149912,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDExODE0OTkxMg==","user":{"login":"dan-fitzgerald-av","id":3443800,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM0NDM4MDA=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3443800?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/dan-fitzgerald-av","html_url":"https://github.com/dan-fitzgerald-av","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dan-fitzgerald-av/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dan-fitzgerald-av/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dan-fitzgerald-av/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dan-fitzgerald-av/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dan-fitzgerald-av/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dan-fitzgerald-av/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dan-fitzgerald-av/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dan-fitzgerald-av/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dan-fitzgerald-av/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2015-07-02T19:57:05Z","updated_at":"2015-07-02T19:57:05Z","body":"On an lines that aren't the widest line of a multi-line, center aligned BitmapFont, some of the glyphs get garbled as seen in the \"M\" of \"TIME\" in the first image or the \"W\" of \"WHIP.\" \n\nThere appears to be both vertical and horizontal issues in the line that say \"143 Enemies\" here:\n![java 2015-07-02 14-02-23-80](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/3443800/8485629/989d4068-20c4-11e5-95f5-6f598cc1c9d4.png)\n\nFor reference, here's a still from the old version of the game, which used 1.5.5, before the big BitmapFont overhaul:\n![cap1 avi_snapshot_07 20_ 2015 07 02_14 17 25](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/3443800/8486106/ff30d878-20c7-11e5-8c92-04d847241337.png)\n\nBased on some tweaks I had just made to my own text wrapper class' alignment offset code (I was seeing similar issues in even single line text at first,) I'm fairly certain that the change I suggested to GlyphLayout will fix the issue. Here is the edit I would make (I added three lines):\n\n```\n        // line 200 in GlyphLayout as of 1.6.3\n        // Align runs to center or right of targetWidth.\n        if ((halign & Align.left) == 0) { // Not left aligned, so must be center or right aligned.\n            boolean center = (halign & Align.center) != 0;\n            boolean integer = font.usesIntegerPositions(); // Added this line\n            float lineWidth = 0, lineY = Integer.MIN_VALUE;\n            int lineStart = 0, n = runs.size;\n            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {\n                GlyphRun run = runs.get(i);\n                if (run.y != lineY) {\n                    lineY = run.y;\n                    float shift = targetWidth - lineWidth;\n                    if (center) shift /= 2;\n                    if (integer) shift = Math.round(shift); // Added this line\n                    while (lineStart < i)\n                        runs.get(lineStart++).x += shift;\n                    lineWidth = 0;\n                }\n                lineWidth += run.width;\n            }\n            float shift = targetWidth - lineWidth;\n            if (center) shift /= 2;\n            if (integer) shift = Math.round(shift); // Added this line\n            while (lineStart < n)\n                runs.get(lineStart++).x += shift;\n        }\n```\n\nI tried reproducing it with the built in arial-15 font but the issue wasn't apparent as it is with a low res pixel font like I'm using. Do I need to make and upload a test project that includes the .fnt and textures to reproduce? Should I be doing a pull request instead?\n","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/libgdx/libgdx/issues/comments/118149912/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes"