 integer = font.usesIntegerPositions(); // Added this line\n>         float lineWidth = 0, lineY = Integer.MIN_VALUE;\n>         int lineStart = 0, n = runs.size;\n>         for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {\n>             GlyphRun run = runs.get(i);\n>             if (run.y != lineY) {\n>                 lineY = run.y;\n>                 float shift = targetWidth - lineWidth;\n>                 if (center) shift /= 2;\n>                 if (integer) shift = Math.round(shift); // Added this line\n>                 while (lineStart < i)\n>                     runs.get(lineStart++).x += shift;\n>                 lineWidth = 0;\n>             }\n>             lineWidth += run.width;\n>         }\n>         float shift = targetWidth - lineWidth;\n>         if (center) shift /= 2;\n>         if (integer) shift = Math.round(shift); // Added this line\n>         while (lineStart < n)\n>             runs.get(lineStart++).x += shift;\n>     }\n> ```\n> \n> I tried reproducing it with the built in arial-15 font but the issue\n> wasn't apparent as it is with a low res pixel font like I'm using. Do I\n> need to make and upload a test project that includes the .fnt and textures\n> to reproduce? Should I be doing a pull request instead?\n> \n> â€”\n> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub\n> https://github.com/libgdx/libgdx/issues/3254#issuecomment-118149912.\n","author_association":"MEMBER","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/libgdx/libgdx/issues/comments/118377093/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"NathanSweet","id":434010,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQzNDAxMA==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/434010?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet","html_url":"https://github.com/NathanSweet","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/NathanSweet/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/libgdx/libgdx/issues/comments/118406959","html_url":"https://github.com/libgdx/libgdx/issues/3254#issuecomment-118406959","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/libgdx/libgdx/issues/3254","id":118406959,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDExODQwNjk1OQ==","user":{"login":"dan-fitzgerald-av","id":3443800,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM0NDM4MDA=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3443800?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/dan-fitzgerald-av","html_url":"https://github.com/dan-fitzgerald-av","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dan-fitzgerald-av/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dan-fitzgerald-av/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dan-fitzgerald-av/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dan-fitzgerald-av/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dan-fitzgerald-av/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dan-fitzgerald-av/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dan-fitzgerald-av/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dan-fitzgerald-av/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dan-fitzgerald-av/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2015-07-03T18:37:50Z","updated_at":"2015-07-03T18:37:50Z","body":"Thanks for the reply Nathan!\n\nI think I figured it out, and I stand by my original suggestion (although I think I have a neater one now.)\n\nWhen an x or y value that ends in a .5 is passed to the `addGlyph` method in BitmapFontCache, there's a good chance that the resulting x and x2 or y and y2 will round in opposite directions, causing issues like mine. This is why I had to start rounding my own offset values after updating to the new BitmapFont refactor, and why GlyphLayout's centering is causing me issues.\n\nMy new suggestion is to round `gx` and `gy` in the `addToCache` method in BitmapFontCache. There might still be rounding errors with the spacing between glyphs and/or runs, though, so maybe there should be rounding further up the chain!\n\nAnother solution might be to use floor instead of round, but I haven't fully thought that through.\n","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/libgdx/libgdx/issues/comments/118406959/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"dan-fitzgerald-av","id":3443800,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM0NDM4MDA=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3443800?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/dan-fitzgerald-av","html_url":"https://github.com/dan-fitzgerald-av","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dan-fitzgerald-av/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dan-fitzgerald-av/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dan-fitzgerald-av/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dan-fitzgerald-av/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dan-fitzgerald-av/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dan-fitzgerald-av/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dan-fitzgerald-a